commitResults.messageTitle: Added functionality for Level-1.
Added functionality for Level-2. Added some comments to the code.
Added functionality for Level-3
Addded functionality for Level-4
Added functionality for Level-5.
Added functionality for Level-6

Added functionality for Level-7. - Created a DukeSaveLoad class to handle the saving and loading of data - Created "toSaveFileString" methods for Task class to help with saving and loading of data - Edited Duke to save data whenever its internal list changes

Added functionality for Level-8 - Created DukeDateTime class to handle all date and time computation - Edited Duke's input parsing to work with specific formats for date and time - Edited EventTask and DeadlineTask to use DukeDateTime to encode timings - Fixed a bug where TaskList would use the user input index rather than the actual index to complete tasks

Refactored code to be cleaner + better fitting to OOP standards. - Decision-making moved out of Duke into UserInputProcessor - Created TextToTaskTranslator to parse Text inputs into Tasks (Text -> Task translation no longer part of Decision-Making) - Duke's text lines moved out of Duke into DukeUi - Deleted all custom Exceptions other than DukeException - All DukeExceptions, rather than having a hard-coded error message, will call upon the appropriate error message in DukeUi during instantiation. - Changed DukeSaveLoad (and all saving and loading operations to use "Serializable" rather than String-parsing) - Changed Task from an Interface to an Abstract Class, changed each Task accordingly - Changed implementation of DukeDateTime and created - Created DukeDuration class - EventTask uses DukeDuration to keep track of its timing - Added "Nuke" functionality to Duke to allow it to destroy all Tasks in the list
Implemented Increment A-JUnit - Ported project over into Maven in order to use JUnit - Created tests for DukeReply and ToDoTask classes

Added functionality for Level-9 - Added ability for UserInputProcessor to recognise and parse 'Find' command   - Added 'processFindCase' method   - Added 'Find' to userInputType enum - Added FEEDBACK_FIND and FEEDBACK_FIND_NOTHING Strings to DukeUi. - Added 'descriptionContainsTerm' method to Task - Added 'getMatchingTasksAsString' method to TaskList
Refactored code to be closer to the Java Coding Standard: https://nus-cs2103-ay1920s1.github.io/website/coding-standards/java/intermediate.html
Revert "Refactored code to be closer to the Java Coding Standard:"
Refactored code to abide more closely to module Coding Standard: https://nus-cs2103-ay1920s1.github.io/website/coding-standards/java/intermediate.html
Added javadoc comments for all classes in the project.

Housekeeping - Implemented serialVersionUID for Serializable classes - Added comments explaining use of private methods - Create javadoc comments for Level-9 methods (related to Find functionality) - Abstracted out checkIndexExists method to check for exceptions in TaskList - Replaced using equals("") with using isEmpty() to check for empty Strings
port project over from Maven to Gradle
Implement JavaFX - Followed the tutorials. - The cute animals are placeholders. Don't get used to them.
Added Assertions - Added two assertions in descriptionContainsTerm method for abstract class Task.

Made changes to ensure Code Quality - Deleted unused, commented out code - Deprecated the DukeTextFormatter, since the project has moved from console to GUI - Abstracted out checkCommandIncludesIndex method in UserInputProcessor - Abstracted out bothStartAndEndDateExist boolean in translateTaskEvent method for better readability.

Added functionality for Notes - Added commands for adding, deleting and display notes - Duke now holds a reference to a NoteList - Added relevant lines to DukeUi - DukeSaveLoad saves 2 separate files - a NoteList and a TaskList
Add support for ShadowJar so that standalone jar file will include JavaFX files - Edited build.gradle
